sql:
SELECT reservoirs.name, users.user_name 
FROM reservoirs 
JOIN users ON reservoirs.administrator_id = users.user_id;

SELECT user_id, user_name, email, role
FROM users
WHERE user_id NOT IN (SELECT user_id FROM team_members);

SELECT name, capacity, current_storage, (current_storage - target_storage) AS storage_difference
FROM reservoirs
WHERE (current_storage - target_storage) >= 10000;

SELECT *
FROM reservoirs
WHERE capacity > (SELECT AVG(capacity) FROM reservoirs);

SELECT user_name, email 
FROM users 
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM team_members);

external_knowledge:
- Golden apples: metaphor for valid data entries;
- Orchard of quality checks: the `data_quality_checks` table;
- An apple is considered golden (valid) if its `is_valid` indicator is set to `1`.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) as valid_data_count
FROM data_quality_checks
WHERE is_valid = 1;
